Creates the bounds given the southwest corner [min]
and the northeast corner [max].

Both [min] are [max] must be objects accepted by
[LatLon.from].

## Examples
    var b1 = new LatLonBounds(new LonLat(0,0), new LonLat(1,1));
    var b1 = new LatLonBounds([0,0], [1,1]);
    var b1 = new LatLonBounds({"lon": 0, "lat": 0}, {"lon": 1, "lat": 1});

Creates a lat/lon point from another value [other]. [other] must not be null.

## [other] - possible values

* another [LatLon]
* a [List] with two numbers lat, lon
* a [Map] with two properties `lat` and `lon` of type [num].

## Examples
    var ll1 = new LatLon.from([0, 12.32]);
    var ll2 = new LatLon.from({"lat": 0, "lon": 12.32});
    var ll3 = new LatLon.from(ll1);
